  "prompt": "What does a fuel temperature sensor do in the engine?",
  "response": "A fuel temperature sensor monitors the temperature of the fuel in the fuel system. Its primary functions include:\n\n1. Helping the engine control unit (ECU) adjust fuel injection timing and quantity\n2. Ensuring optimal fuel density and viscosity for efficient combustion\n3. Compensating for fuel temperature variations that can affect engine performance\n4. Supporting fuel system efficiency and preventing potential cold-start or hot-running issues\n5. Providing temperature data that helps calculate precise fuel metering\n\nThe sensor typically sends electronic signals to the ECU, which uses this temperature information to make real-time adjustments to fuel delivery and engine performance.",
